The source of your problem fact that you don&#39;t really understand how arrays work in elastic, from the [docs](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/array.html):
&gt;there is no dedicated array datatype.

Meaning when you index an array (that is not typed [nested](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/nested.html#targetText=The%20nested%20type%20is%20a,queried%20independently%20of%20each%20other.)) you lose the ability to query individual items in it due to the fact that elastic &quot;flattens&quot; the array.

You have two options:

1. The more proper solution is to reindex your data, make sentence to be typed [nested](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/nested.html#targetText=The%20nested%20type%20is%20a,queried%20independently%20of%20each%20other), then you can query each item individually.

