Change your vertex shader to the following:

    #version 410
    layout (location=0) in vec3 position;
    uniform vec3 displace; // new!
    void main(void) {
        gl_Position = vec4(displace + position, 1.0f);
    }

This modifies the vertex positions according to the value of the `displace` [uniform variable](https://www.khronos.org/opengl/wiki/Uniform_(GLSL)).

In your render loop:

    GLint u_displace = glGetUniformLocation(renderingProgram, &quot;displace&quot;);

    glBindVertexArray(VAOs[0]);
    glUniform3f(u_displace, 0, 0, 0); 
    glDrawArrays(GL_TRIANGLES, 0, 3);

    glBindVertexArray(VAOs[1]);
    glUniform3f(u_displace, 0, 0.25, 0); 
    glDrawArrays(GL_TRIANGLES, 0, 3);
    glBindVertexArray(0);

This will set the value of the &quot;displace&quot; uniform to (0,0,0) for the first square, and (0, 0.25, 0) for the second, effectively drawing it with an offset.

